  "text": "The CSS layout engine reflow pipeline in Mozilla Firefox (gecko-dev) comprises three interconnected subsystems:\n\n**1. FRAME CONSTRUCTION PHASE (layout/base/)**\nThe frame construction subsystem, implemented in nsCSSFrameConstructor.cpp and nsCSSFrameConstructor.h, is responsible for creating the frame tree from the DOM tree. This process:\n- Constructs frames based on CSS display properties\n- Creates anonymous frames for special layout modes (flex, grid, tables)\n- Maintains frame state across construction phases\nThe nsFrameManager.cpp/h files manage the frame tree after construction, handling frame lifecycle and state transitions.\n\n**2. REFLOW PIPELINE (layout/generic/)**\nThe reflow system is the core layout computation engine:\n\n**ReflowInput/ReflowOutput** (ReflowInput.cpp/h, ReflowOutput.cpp/h):\n- ReflowInput contains all input parameters for a reflow operation (constraints, parent state, float information)\n- ReflowOutput contains the computed metrics (size, overflow, baseline) returned from reflow\n\n**BlockReflowState** (BlockReflowState.cpp/h):\n- Encapsulates state during block-level frame reflow\n- Manages float handling and clear operations\n- Tracks line breaking and margin collapsing\n\n**nsBlockFrame** (nsBlockFrame.cpp/h):\n- Core implementation of block-level layout\n- Handles reflow of block, inline, and float children\n- Implements line breaking and text wrapping logic\n- DoReflowInlineFrames and ReflowBlock are key methods\n\n**nsBlockReflowContext** (nsBlockReflowContext.cpp/h):\n- Context for reflowing individual block children\n- Handles margin collapsing and positioning\n\n**nsLineLayout** (nsLineLayout.cpp/h) and **nsLineBox** (nsLineBox.cpp/h):\n- Manage inline-level frame layout and line box creation\n- Handle baseline alignment and text measurement\n\n**nsInlineFrame** (nsInlineFrame.cpp/h):\n- Implements inline-level container layout\n- Delegates to line layout for content arrangement\n\n**nsFloatManager** (nsFloatManager.cpp/h):\n- Manages float positioning and clearing\n- Maintains float regions for float avoidance calculations\n- Essential for block layout's float handling\n\n**AbsoluteContainingBlock** (AbsoluteContainingBlock.cpp/h):\n- Handles layout of absolutely and fixed-positioned children\n- Computes absolute positioning constraints\n\n**nsPlaceholderFrame** (nsPlaceholderFrame.cpp/h):\n- Placeholder for out-of-flow frames (floats, positioned elements)\n- Links out-of-flow frames to their containing blocks\n\n**3. DIRTY FRAME INVALIDATION & FRAME STATE (layout/generic/)**\nThe frame state system tracks which frames need reflow:\n\n**nsFrameStateBits.h**:\n- Defines state bits used to mark frames as dirty\n- NS_FRAME_IS_DIRTY: Frame needs full reflow\n- NS_FRAME_HAS_DIRTY_CHILDREN: At least one child is dirty\n- NS_FRAME_FIRST_REFLOW: Frame hasn't been reflowed yet\n- NS_FRAME_IN_REFLOW: Frame is currently being reflowed\n- NS_FRAME_REFLOW_ROOT: Frame can be a reflow root for dynamic reflows\n\n**nsFrameState.cpp/h**:\n- Implementation of frame state bit management\n- Methods to set, clear, and query state bits\n\n**nsIFrame.cpp/h**:\n- Base frame interface with methods:\n  - MarkSubtreeDirty(): Mark frame and descendants as dirty\n  - IsSubtreeDirty(): Check if frame or descendants are dirty\n  - ChildIsDirty(): Called when a child frame becomes dirty\n  - DidReflow(): Clear dirty bits after reflow completion\n  - InvalidateFrame(): Request visual invalidation\n\n**4. REFLOW ORCHESTRATION (layout/base/)**\n**PresShell** (PresShell.cpp/h):\n- Main entry point for reflow operations\n- FrameNeedsReflow(): Mark frame dirty and schedule reflow\n- Manages reflow batching and scheduling\n- Coordinates with RestyleManager for style changes\n\n**nsPresContext** (nsPresContext.cpp/h):\n- Presentation context containing reflow state\n- Tracks reflow metrics and invalidated regions\n\n**nsRefreshDriver** (nsRefreshDriver.cpp/h):\n- Coordinates screen update timing (vsync)\n- Orchestrates style recalculation and reflow phases\n- Manages reflow callbacks via nsIReflowCallback.h\n\n**5. HELPER COMPONENTS**\n**ViewportFrame** (ViewportFrame.cpp/h) and **nsCanvasFrame** (nsCanvasFrame.cpp/h):\n- Root frame types that manage the viewport and canvas\n\n**nsFrameList** (nsFrameList.cpp/h):\n- Efficient doubly-linked list for frame management\n\nThe pipeline operates as follows:\n1. Style changes trigger PresShell::FrameNeedsReflow(), which marks frames with dirty bits\n2. nsRefreshDriver::Tick() initiates the reflow phase\n3. PresShell::DoReflow() processes dirty frames from root to leaves\n4. nsCSSFrameConstructor handles frame construction when needed\n5. Block/inline layout engines (nsBlockFrame, nsLineLayout) compute positions/sizes\n6. Float manager and absolute positioning handle special layout modes\n7. Dirty bits are cleared after reflow completes in DidReflow()\n8. Paint invalidation occurs for changed regions\n\nThis architecture enables efficient incremental layout updates by only reflowing dirty subtrees while maintaining layout correctness through careful frame state management."
}

